### Health check
GET http://localhost:8000/health

###

### Create ticket
POST http://localhost:8000/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "CUST-001",
  "customer_email": "alice@example.com",
  "customer_name": "Alice Smith",
  "subject": "Cannot login to my account",
  "description": "I keep getting an authentication error when trying to login. The password reset email is not arriving either.",
  "category": "account_access",
  "priority": "high",
  "status": "new",
  "tags": ["auth", "login"],
  "metadata": {"source": "web_form", "device_type": "desktop"}
}

###

### Create ticket with auto-classification
POST http://localhost:8000/tickets?auto_classify=true
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "CUST-002",
  "customer_email": "bob@example.com",
  "customer_name": "Bob Jones",
  "subject": "Production is down critical outage affecting all users",
  "description": "All users are unable to access the production system. This is an emergency requiring immediate attention.",
  "tags": ["outage"]
}

###

### Create ticket — validation error (bad email)
POST http://localhost:8000/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "CUST-003",
  "customer_email": "not-an-email",
  "customer_name": "Charlie",
  "subject": "A subject",
  "description": "Short"
}

###

### List all tickets
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets

###

### Filter by category
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets?category=billing_question

###

### Filter by priority
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets?priority=urgent

###

### Filter by status
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets?status=new

###

### Filter by multiple params
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets?category=billing_question&priority=high

###

### Filter by customer_id
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets?customer_id=CUST-001

###

### Get specific ticket (replace ID)
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets/{{ticket_id}}

###

### Update ticket status
PUT http://localhost:8000/tickets/{{ticket_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress",
  "assigned_to": "agent1@support.com"
}

###

### Auto-classify existing ticket
POST http://localhost:8000/tickets/{{ticket_id}}/auto-classify

###

### Delete ticket
DELETE http://localhost:8000/tickets/{{ticket_id}}

###

### Bulk import CSV (adjust file path as needed)
POST http://localhost:8000/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

< tests/fixtures/sample_tickets.csv
--boundary--

###

### Get 404 for nonexistent ticket
GET http://localhost:8000/tickets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
